<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96954142213998></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96954142213998><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=96954142213998>nice hunting tactic i used</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=96954142213998#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Sep 21st 9:03 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>get a cleric.  use a firepet.  cast burnout.  give pet good weapons.  have pet heal spells <br>hotkeyed (both the lower and higher level one if you have both).  have 'pet report<br>health' hotkeyed.  send pet in.  constantly check pet health with hotkey.  tell cleric <br>to cast one heal only when you say 'go' when the pet gets around 60-70% health.  a <br>cleric heal will get the pet up to around 90-100% again.  if mob scores multiple hits and<br>outpaces the clerics heals use yours at the same time.  the pets dd spell, melee, and <br>fireshield especially tear the mob up pretty good especially since you and the cleric just<br>pump in more hit points to the pet to keep it's fireshield cranking out the damage.  some<br>pet buffs are also good beforehand as usual.  simple.  it works.  watch the mobs melt like<br>a stick of butter in a microwave.  if you get real good at it you can know when to use <br>your own heal and when to tell the cleric to use one of his as to minimized medding <br>downtime.  spreads out the mana usage between the two of you.  and while the xp isn't<br>quite as good because of the pet doing most of the damage i feel it's compensated for <br>by the low downtime from good mana usage which results in a faster killing rate for the <br>small group.  i did this with a cleric and held the 3 spawn aviak tower on the hill for about<br>4 hours of game time.  we handled everything up to harriers which where yellow at the <br>time.  avo's = forget it at the level i was doing this.  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
