<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96928903917438></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96928903917438><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=96928903917438>Kunark hunting (Where do you want to hunt today?)</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=96928903917438#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=1517><span id=Scholar>Elrique</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>17 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Sep 18th 10:57 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Some of the best hunting I've found for post 40 hell levels is on this "new" continent.  (Still call it the new continent, and the others the "Older World"...)  :)<br><br>I know where I've been hunting, and want to get a feel of where others are hunting.  Here's a list of some of the better places I've found.<br><br>1) Frountier Mountains:  Thoe whole zone is chock full of medium - to - low blues and can be worked pretty fast.   I like hanging out near the Burning Woods zone, though, since the higher cons tend to be around this area.<br><br>2) Burning Woods:  Just inside the zone from Frountier Mountains.  Lots of higher to mid ranged blues, with even some whites, yellows and reds in range if you so desire them.  (Probably a good idea to hunt this with a partner, though.)<br><br>3) The Overthere:  Most of the mobs here are starting to go green now, and the loot is pathetic, but you can still pick up a little bit of exp here.<br><br>4) The Mines of Nurga: Probably the least used, and most neglected dungeon on the game.  Many times I've been the only one in this zone.  Some of the great hunting spots are right inside the zone, up the right hand waterfall, there are 2 spawn points, and the other location is back in where all the spiders start up, there are 2 sets of spider spawns, with 2 in each loaction that can be split pretty well...  (This is about right to med up between the splits, if you are carefull, adn work the spiders methodically)<br><br>5)The Dreadlands: North Wall.  Just watch out for the dragon that wanders around here.  If you have killed any wurms in Burning Woods you are KOS to this one.<br><br>6) The Temple of Droga: Several spots in here are fun/exciting, even though there are a few greens mixed in.  (This will also take a group to go back in very far.)  The loot here can be either poor, or very good, depending on if you can find the "drop" mobs.  (Shroud of Nature's a pretty good drop, but it's a long camp, I understand, and can be overwhelming to someone soloing)<br><br>These are just a few of the places in Kunark that I have hunted since 40.  I just dinged 46 last night, so I'm not sure if the cons have changed on any of these, though.  <br><br>Let's here from the rest of you about where you are hunting, and how things in those places are going.  Might give the rest of us some ideas, too...  :)<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Elrique Melnebone<br>Elementalist of Blood and Honor<br>Master Vending Machine<br>Veeshan</td></tr>
