<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96843632226511></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96843632226511><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=96843632226511>Fighting Skills</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=96843632226511#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=1402><span id= >SlyFox</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>3 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Sep 8th 2:05 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hail all,<br><br>Many mages i've heard always mention that mages DO NOT FIGHT with their melee skills.<br><br>This is a shame as there are quite some benefits if you train your fight skills.<br><br>POSSIBLE SPOILER FOR YOU SO DO NOT READ ON IF NOT INTERESTED IN HARD FACTS OF SKILLS.<br><br>Tips<br>----<br>1) Start training these skills early on as melee skills only improve against monsters that are at least BLUE.<br>2) It generally takes me up to 2 bubs of experience while soloing to get all my fighting skills maxxed for my current level. Of course this means i was maxed beforehand.<br>In a group that allows me to melee from time to time, it takes me up to 4 bubs to get them maxxed.<br>3) They are hard to train if not started early, but will allow you to protect your pet. Use your Phantom shield(s) after lvl 16.<br>4) You will die a bit more in the short long while training them, but will die less later on. <br>5) I tend to get more skill gains in less occupied zones on average. I might be wrong but it sure has panned out for me that way.<br><br>Effects of Fighting skills<br>--------------------------<br>Dodge<br>--&gt; Lets you dodge from time to time. (no really, hehe).<br><br>Hand-to-Hand + 1H Blunt + 2H Blunt + Piercing + Throwing<br>--&gt; Per 3 skill points, you will have 8 Attack more.<br><br>Offense<br>--&gt; Per 4 skill points, you will have 5 Attack more.<br><br>Defense<br>--&gt; Per 4 skill points, you will have 5 AC more. <br><br>Note: This may not seem like much, but if you add them up over the levels it adds up massively and can save your live more often then not.<br>At lvl 27 without any modifications item-wise or spell-wise.:<br>--&gt; ATK 351 (((84/3)*8)+((108/4)*5)) for 1HB, 2HB and Piercing<br>--&gt; ATK 335 (((75/3)*8)+((108/4)*5)) for Hand-to Hand and Throwing<br>--&gt; AC 120 ((96/4)*5) (additional)<br><br>Maximum as far as i have been able to find out<br>----------------------------------------------<br>Dodge + Hand-to-Hand + Throwing<br>--&gt; max=(75), max per level=(3), max formula per level=((level+1)* 3)<br><br>1H Blunt + 2H Blunt + Piercing<br>--&gt; max=?(&gt;84), max per level=(3), max formula per level=((level+1)*3)<br><br>Offense<br>--&gt; max=?(&gt;108), max per level=(4), max formula per level=(level*4)<br><br>Defense<br>--&gt; max=?(&gt;96), max per level=?(alternates between 3 and 4), max formula per level=?(no clue)<br><br>Conclusion<br>----------<br><br>Do not hesitate to train your skills as long as they still raise as they will make you more durable for critical situations and could possibly save your friends and you.<br>I will enhance this document as I have the definite figures to complete it (rumors are that max for missing items is 110 or 135).<br><br>Take care and good luck all.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>SlyFox, mage</td></tr>
