<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96843329421497></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96843329421497><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=96843329421497>Soloing with Pets from 16-33</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=96843329421497#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=1402><span id= >SlyFox</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>3 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Sep 8th 1:14 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Forenote:<br>---------<br>I will not go into details of the strengths, weakness of the different types of elementals.<br><br>The suggestions of elements focus on the majority of huntingl, i.e. blues to yellows.<br><br>This document is valid for elementals of lvl 19-33 of which i know something about.<br>Lvl 34+ is a slightly different ballgame especially as the majority of hunting is either grouping or blue-hunting while soloing. Any additions by higher level players would be welcome here.<br><br>You can solo with each elemental and each one has their advantage. Your success lies in learning how to accomodate your pets strengths and weaknesses as well as your playstyle (camp, explore and hunt, try new things, etc.).<br><br>For soloing ask yourself the following questions:<br>A) Do you cast a lot of damaging spells as quickly as possible?<br>B) Do you cast some damage spells, but time them so you don't overaggro the opponent?<br>c) Are you hunting in an area you can not run or flee (i.e small island, dungeon, many monsters that will attack close by, etc.)?<br>d) Are the monsters you're fighting very aggressive (i.e. generally humanoids are more aggressive than animals)?<br>e) Are the monsters you are fighting poisonous?<br>f) Are the monsters you are fighting casters?<br>g) Are the monsters you are fighting blues, whites or yellows?<br>h) Are the monsters you are fighting less protected against fire?<br><br>EARTH<br>-----<br>A) Yes.<br>B) No.<br>c) + d) You tend more to Yes.<br>e) No.<br>f) not relevant.<br>g) mainly blues and whites.<br>h) not relevant.<br>These answers show that you aggro the monster very heavily and thus the monster will be completely fixated on you. The regen of the pet is quite slow and tends to increase my meditation times.<br>The 'Rooting' allows you more safety and different techniques in Kiting.<br><br>WATER<br>-----<br>A) No.<br>B) Yes.<br>c) + d) You tend more to No.<br>e) Yes.<br>f) not relevant<br>g) not relevant (i.e. blue, whites and yellows)<br>h) not relevant<br>These ansers show that you carefully cast your spells and don't aggro the monsters much. The monster will be generally fixated on your Water pet. The regen of the pet is awesome and tends to lessen your downtime.<br>This teaches you a valuable lesson of how to hunt with non-Rooting monster. This is something you will be doing more often as you advance into the higher levels.<br><br>AIR<br>---<br>A) No.<br>B) Yes.<br>c) + d) You tend more to No.<br>e) No.<br>f) Yes.<br>g) mainly blues.<br>h) not relevant.<br>The Stun effect is very useful against casters, however the Air elemental is not really made for Soloing up to lvl 33.<br><br>Fire<br>----<br>A) No.<br>B) Yes.<br>c) + d) You tend more to No.<br>e) No.<br>f) No.<br>g) mainly blues.<br>h) Yes.<br>The Fire elemental is only useful for soloing against monsters with low fire protection. They become much more useful for soloing after 34.<br><br>My hunting<br>----------<br>I have been mainly using the Water pet for soloing purposes from lvl 12 up to my current lvl and have done quite well with it as soon as i learned not to overaggro.<br>I personally think it has improved my hunting in groups as well. The only time i get aggroed nowadays is when a monster gets created closest to me or when i actively perform it to pull a monster of a group member.<br>The Water seems to give me less downtime as i melee in between with Phantom shield leather on, thus protecting my pet and improving his already awesome regen even more.<br><br>Finally enjoy the game while you can as leveling for leveling sake takes quite a bit out of the game (at least for me).<br><br>Disclaimers<br>-----------<br><br>Most of this document is based on experiences i've personally had and through many of the tales / insights i've seen on other boards or in the game.<br>&nbsp;<br>SlyFox, mage</td></tr>
