	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, here is my 2cps worth. I worked up my tailoring skills to make raw silk. It works fine. :) Im lvl 20 now tho, and I do like to fight, despite the severe combat limitations of this class. I kept advancing my tailoring skill and am now making cured silk. Cured silk is excellent mid level armor, with AC of 5 pretty much across the board. Now, what to do with it? Well, there are a lot of casters out there. And there are a lot of newbies. I sell cured silk off for about 1pp per piece of clothes, and gold for about 5gp per piece of clothes, only to offset the cost and time. (ie, brewing heady kiolas for cured and hunting spiderwebs for raw and cured). What else do I use my money for? Well, my advice - Move to freeport and start working on that blacksmith skill. I am currently about lvl 115 in blacksmithing, and am almost ready to attempt the apex of armor - the new elven chain mail line. This stuff is hard to make and expensive if you fail, so you should only try it if you are a master blacksmith. However, the stats on this @#%^ is amazing. Its also magical, so it has properties Im not sure of. Only downside is it is class specific. If you are a HE for example, you can only forge HE armor at a forge in Felwithe, etc. still. this @#%^ SELLS ITSELF :) What mage wouldnt want a nice AC9 piece of armor? from what I heard, it isnt even all that heavy. I mean collectively Im sure it can be, but hell, just get st increasing items. :) <br><br>This wonderful website has all sorts of guides about how to be a blacksmith.. it takes a long time to learn and it is expensive, but if you move to freeport and hunt in lavastorm a lot, you will be able to not only make and sell the best possible magical armor for your race, but you will be able to make all sorts of cool armor for other races that can significantly increase your number of friends and your cash influx. :) <br><br>Nahualli<br><br>Elemental Master of the 20th Summon<br>Tarrew Marr<br>&nbsp;<br>