	   <tr><td colspan=2>Okay I would like to point out that this last post made me sound like a moron.. I am revising it now. <br><br>First of all, my apologies.. I had posted this as a hypothetical situation, but when I actually put into practice, it was much different. First of all, I went ahead and bought a LOT of Kiola Sap (available at most bars, its a POUCH dont look for anything in a BOTTLE, a lot of empty bottles and a lot of water. I sat my ass in front of that brew barrel and swore I was going to make Heady Kiolas. I didnt realize that you shouldnt attempt HKs anytime before lvl 28. Oh well.. trial and error, and I am now lvl 25 in brewing, and I had a whole @#%^load of heady kiolas. By the way, if you fail at a HK, you lose the water and sap, you keep the bottle. <br><br>Then I started to work on the cured silk. Successfully made a gorget and sandals on my first try, then failed for about 20 more tries. It got kinda expensive and I ran out of spider silks. I headed out to EC to try to find more silks, and tried to wear the cured silk. heh heh heh. I then realized its MONK ONLY. I thought well Ill be damned. I turned to the zone and announced that any noob that tagged me first at the FP gates would get a cured silk gorget and sandals for free. NO ONE answered. I thought fine, Ill sell it to a vendor. I sold the gorget off for 5 golds, but held on to the sandals... I dont like selling stuff back that someone else can use... and I announced again. This dude, lvl 26 monk walks up and pokes me. I say "noobs only sorry" he says "Oh I want to buy them off you for 20 plats". Im thinking @#%^! so he bought them off me. 20 plats! I was floored. Having found some more silk, I proceeded to make a cured silk Gi, the tunic/robe thingy. first off the AC on it is 8, but the weight is negligible. It is also a MONK ONLY item. I EFFORTLESSLY sold it off for 35pp. Sold a cloak and pants off for another 40pp. So.. in ONE DAY, with stuff I was ready to give away and even destroy, I made 95 plats! Now, this is no gold mine, and it wont buy you no totemic armor, but hey, if I invest some serious concentration into this, I can rake in several hundred plats per day! You are only limited, with cured silk... by the number of monks that are being played. :) Remember, both human and Iksar can play monks... the only bad part is that iksar monks have an incredibly hard life... by the time they make it to Freeport, they more often than not have decent gear already. Something to be said about promoting monkhood. :) LOL<br><br>Nahualli <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
