<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96810958323045></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96810958323045><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=96810958323045>Thought for Magi around 30</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=96810958323045#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=759><span id=Scholar>Adiemus</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>48 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Sep 4th 7:19 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.88]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I wanted to share what was a very effective strategy with all of you.<br><br>I play a druid and I managed to get into a basment group in Unrest the other night. Sharing my group were two tanks, another druid, a cleric (were we lucky or what?) and a magician. Our levels ranged from 29 to 33. <br><br>Upon breaking the initial full basement spawn, we set down to pull individual MoBs as they showed up. Our magician summoned an Air Pet and armed it with twin Gnoll-Hide Lariats. As any of you familiar with the basement in Unrest know, Festering Hags are probably the worst of what spawns there- not many HP, but they have a very nasty Force Shock spell that I think does upward of 300 points damage. Well, our magician's pet took care of that- you know that air pets cast stun which interrupts both attacks AND spells. Add to the pet's spell the twin stun procs of the 2 gnoll hide lariats, and the Hag's never got a spell off! It made fignting them, if not a pleasure, at least tolerable. The lariat's price has dropped to around 5pp each now, so they are pretty cost-effective (unless you have a tendency to lose pets alot- then could get a bit costly).<br><br>I implore all of you magicians out there to carefully consider your choice of pet when in a group. If your group is to face a caster, do them a favor and summon an Air pet to reduce the number of spells you'll have to absorb.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
