<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96799930531339></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96799930531339><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=96799930531339>Sister Island</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=96799930531339#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=887><span id=Sage>Zuranthium</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>385 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Sep 3rd 12:41 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.56]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I totally fogot about a GREAT place to hunt in my huge guide. Sister Island! I'll tell ya whats good about it:<br><br>At level 10 a magician not wanting to hunt wisps can come here. You get to sister island by taking the boat from freeport to butcherblock. The first stop(only one really) that the boat makes is sister island. If you are a dark elf magician you will have to jump off the boat before it docks, becuase there is a level 25 sister right on the dock that will whack you if you get off the boat.<br><br>There are level 7-13 sisters roaming all over the island. A level 10 magician can beat the level 13 ones. They run very fast, so you will want to have your pet guard at the shore than then pull at maximum distance with your shock spell, and then run back to the pet and kill the sister. The loot is VERY good for this level. They drop rusty halberds that can be given to your pet to make them do 20 damage a hit, or they can be sold for 3 gold to a merchant. The sister also drop purity belts almost every time. They can be sold to a vendor for a little over a PP. The danger of this is that the sisters help eahc other out, and there is a level 15/16 pirate wandering around that will kick your butt if your low on mana.<br><br>You will be able to get to level 16 killing sisters if you don't feel like hunting wisps or going to the 2x siren spawn that is also in the zone. Sisters a little more risky than the other two options, but if you feel like danger, go for it.<br><br>Sister Island doesn't have anything to offer a magician from levels 16-21, so you won't won't to come here then. At level 22 you can come back and start hunting bigger sisters. Near the shore by the dock there is a level 22-24 sister named Antime. A level 22 magician can camp her and get to level 24(although the hermit in south karana gives better exp.). Once you get to 24 on her you can start killing dwarves, or other sisters. There is one sister standing on the dock and another standing by a tree that is by the dock.  You can camp these girls from level 24 all the way to level 36. At level 36 they will con green, however, so the exp. will become bad. Be sure to pull they away from each other, and to the shore, becuase they WILL assist each other.<br><br>There are also 3 level 24/25 dwarves on the island. At level 24 you will only be able to take 2 of them, and even then you won't be able to fully keep up with the spawns. Once you get to level 29 you will be able to take two of them, and keep them dead. At 34 you will be able to take all 3. These, like the sisters, will get you to level 36 before the exp. is bad.<br><br>Overall: A VERY good spot for the level 22-35 magician, and a decent spot for a level 10-15 magician.<br><br>Things to Remember: Don't forget to outdamage your pet. If you don't, it will steal half of your exp. for the kill. Killing sisters drops your faction with the wood elves and high elves. If you are a dark elf your already KOS, so it doesn't matter. If your not a dark elf, and don't want to become KOS, then don't kill the sisters on the island, just the dwarves. Killing the dwarves will drop your faction, but not with dwarven guards. KIlling the dwarves ont his isaldn will make you KOS to a few useless NPCS in south kaladim. So you shouldn't worry about becoming KOS, it won't hurt you.<br><br>ENJOY!<br><br>Corpusnuntia/Divineshadow/Zuranthium/Plantmaster/Naltec/Natalos/Sunsong<br><br>Player of many characters on the Nameless server.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
