	   <tr><td colspan=2>IMHO, it is an exploit because it's using an error in the game to gain an advantage over the environment that Verant did not put in.  ok, I admit it, I use it too, but that doesn't make it right.  <br><br>Basically if you're using the strafe-run technique, you're moving diagonally in a straight line like this:<br><br>Point                Point<br>A--------------------B<br><br>But (and this is only my guess, but it seems plausible) mobs can't run in a straight line diagonally, due to programming and/or pathing constraints; they more than likely have to move diagonally like this:<br><br>Point                 Point<br>A/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\B<br><br>Since "-" is shorter than "/\" to get to the same point, you actually start putting distance between you and the mob (something I've noticed).<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
