	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Aug 26th 5:10 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.66]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>This is a small post to explain how to be a usefull magician in general.  This is also a tip for higher level mages.<br>----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br><br>Master summoner, a mage can summon all the essential gear he needs for battle.  I mean common, 5 ac necklace, 4 ac rings, a dagger or staves.  This is what you call usefull summoning.<br><br>Among these, the mage is a good person to know in a dungeon or a zone where you can't get the goods you need.<br><br>What am I talking about you say?<br>Basic essentials off course!<br><br>Every item a mage summons has beneficial value:<br><br>Daggers, Staves, Stones, Food/Water, Bands, Bags<br>Arrows, Swords.. and so on.<br><br>Now what does a monk or warrior do with no healer? Bands off course.. lots and lots of bands.<br><br>Now we may not be able to sell clarity or sow as well as enchanter or druids but coldstones, runed swords, and levitation rings do sell well.  Even a stack of bandages earned me 5pp.  The wonderful part about bandages is its 1 extra band per every 2 levels of the mage.  A level 40 can summon a stack in 1 cast and sell it off pretty easy.<br><br>Or how about a dimensional whole with 20 food(cornucopia) or 20 water (everfount) for some plat.  Nice isnt it?<br><br>Even rangers and warriors message me for arrows.  Why? because were there, we can summon the item  cheap, fast, and plenty of them.<br><br>----------------------------------------------<br>Tips for 29+ mages<br>----------------------------------------------<br><br>From my experiences, it was safe to show your level until 29 or so before getting extreme newbie spam and request for gear.<br><br>Until level 39 it wasnt that bad but then the request hit me hard as soon as i'm recognized as a 40+ mage.<br><br>At level 44, my whole bar of mana will dissappear if I sit non/anon in a newbie zone.<br><br>At oasis docks, I went normal for 10 min and had at least 3 /tells a minute for bandages, cold stones, and swords of runes.<br><br>Now all of those who have necro's out there, yes all of you who might read this post, you know you drool at the availability of procing swords for your pets.  You never stop spamming me, swords, Swords.. SwOrDS!...<br><br>Most people would tell me "just tell them no", but would you really want 20 people messaging you anyways for goods???<br>Of course not.  <br><br>So anon or roleplay is the way to go and just /tell a person if he shouts for a needed summon.<br><br>-------------------------------------------------<br>Final commentary.<br>-------------------------------------------------<br><br>Mages rock, they are balanced, have offensive power, and can summon essential and usefull gear.<br>Like shamans for a group who can buff any stat, we can provide almost any basic item needed.<br><br>We are group friendly by providing a tank and magical damage at the same time.  We can take some hits, not much, and most of all fire shield the tanks.<br><br>We certainly do have a down side of no special mana regen or escape method if pet-less.  But a good mage would not be caught without a pet or at least would gate out if pet was dying.<br><br>Good luck to all of you starting a mage, my final tip to you is dont put any points into your stamina,agility,dexterity,wisdom,charisma when making a mage.  Thats how I partially screwed myself, but any minor mistake can be fixed by item equips.  :)<br><br>p.s.(put 5-10 in str and 15-20 in int)<br><br>p.s.s(Zuranthium I would be a sage too if I clicked all my posts with excellents at work &gt;:P<br>j/k nice job....) <br>&nbsp;<br>Eendyar Soulseeker<br>46'th High Elf Mage <br>"Mythic Synergy"<br><a href="http://www.mythicsynergy.com" target=_new>http://www.mythicsynergy.com</a><br>Fennin Ro</td></tr>
