	   <tr><td colspan=2>Im sorry I had to correct you - its just i have a monk character in addition to my mage and i hate how people assume that monks and warriors are just the same but monks dont use weapons or aromor but have cool magical attacks.  Monks have many skills that warriors dont (i.e. Sneak, feign death, safe fall, block, intimidation, mend, etc..) and are more proficient in dodge, dual wield, double attack, and kick; then they have all their monk moves like tiger claw, eagle strike, dragon punch, round kick, and flying dragon kick (most of these are magical).  Im not trying to dis warriors or anything - but monks have some skills they dont - so they arent just another tank that rock in all the weapons and can wear awesome armor; they can heal themselves with mend, survive with feign death, dont need levitate to go through a desert, can scare their foes away, sneak by KOS NPC's, and block attacks.  Because of these "special" skills and magical attacks, monks make better solo classes than most people think (not until they get feign death though) and shouldnt be grouped with other tanks as just an all-around weapons master who cant heal themselves or feign death.<br><br>               - A monk proud of his abilities<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
