	   <tr><td colspan=2>Useless? Well, they're useful in limited situations but I find them useful!<br><br>Sword of runes: The most asked-for . . . after all, the Necros need something to arm their pets with! And not to mention I toss them on my pet as well.<br>Waterstone. I use this a lot around Ocean of Tears, and had the occasion to use one getting into The Hole.<br>Ring of Flight. USEFUL a lot when travelling; you run over water in OoT or lava in Lavastorm or Solusek. No falling damage in badly hilly places like Dagnor's Cauldron or any of the Desert areas. PLUS they have AC so hand them to your pet ;)<br>Coldstone: Hm . . . humans ask for a lot of these . . .<br>Dagger of Symbols: When I need a dagger, I reach for one of these . . .<br>Arrows and throwing daggers: Somehow the puller always asks for these.<br>The other things: Heatstones and staves, are just outclassed by the rest of this stuff.<br><br>Yeah, the pets are great fighters and even better when paired with what's uncommonly called a 'meat shield'. But which pet really shines is the Earth type. Root the mob, I have my best spell ready, and nuke away.<br>The only thing is necros always seem to get their earlier than I do in terms of level . . .<br><br>Jiriki<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
