<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96730656520532></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96730656520532><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=96730656520532>Magician Guide 1-26</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=96730656520532#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Aug 26th 12:16 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.75]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>       Many people will say that a magician is a combination of a Wizard and a Warrior, this is simply not true.  The Magician is more than that, it is the most powerful class in all of norrath.<br><br>When you look at the races you can select for your magician the erudites stick out as having much better stats thean the other races but are blind at night.  If you really care about night sight then be a gnome.  Humans gain levels faster than other races but have miserable stats.  Nights sight can be remedy at lvl 16 so blindness is not as bad as it seems.  For the purposes of this guide i'll assume you were an erudite or human. if you chose gnome or high-elf (bad choice IMO) read the extremely long magician guide which will tell you what to do.<br>    If you were an erudite turn in your guild note and travel to qeynos where you will ask for a bind.  Now go to North Qeynos and kill newbie monster monsters until you reach level 4. Always have minor shielding on, it will save you many times.<br>   Now erudites must travel back to erudin in order to train in meditation while humans need only go to their guild.  You should purchase the spells;Summon Food, water, and dagger from your level one rank and Gate, Elmantalkin Earth, summon bandages and Burn.<br>   Now travel to BlackBurrow in Qeynos hills, there you will kill the gnolls that spawn outside of the dungeon.  You should give your pet any weapons the gnolls drop.  Your strategy should be send your pet to attack with /pet kill and cast burn TWICE and then move in to melee with your pet.  With this method you should be able to kill all 3 faster than they spawn.  keep any gnoll teeth that they drop and sell the weapons and cloth armor.  At lvl 6 you will be ready to venture into black burrow, called BB for short.<br>     BB is a dungeon, which means that deep in the cavaerns monsters almost 10 levels higher than you riseside.  If someone shouts train, that means go to the zone because they're bringing up those monsters, called mobs for short, and a bunch of their friends.  Where you want to fight is the bridge, go to the door that leads deeper into the dungeon and follow that path until you come to the bottom that area is called the bridge.  You can kill almost all the gnolls that spawn in that area with little difficulty use the same stragegy you used on the gnolls outside except you may wish to burn more while you are meleeing.  Kill these until you hit 8.  Go back to Qeynos and give the gnoll tetth that you kept to Captain tillin this will give you gobs of xp and moonstones, now take the moonstones to mcNeal Jocub in fish's bar and he will give you BlackBurrow stout which you can sell to him for about 7 silver.  <br>   Your level 8 spells are a serious investment at 4-5pp a pop.  Just buy Elementaling earth, shock of blades, shield of fire, and lesser shielding; if you have the money.  Now return to BlackBurrow and go to the bridge, now go around the lake to the right, avioding the gnolls until you come to another door.  follow that path up until you come to an open space, that is where giant snakes spawn and you will be killing these.  Send you pet to attack and give him the shield of fire burn generously with shock of baldes and use /pet report health when he reaches 40% jump in and melee.  You can rest safely on the ledge where one of the snakes spawn.  they drop snake fangs, keep one for yourself and sell the rest to merchants.  Kill these until level 10 where you will give black burrow a farewell and travel to the island in erud's crossing where willowisps will be your target, these are relitively easy and you can solo them up to lvl 16. destroy the burned out lightstones they drop sell the regular ones to the catman on the island and keep the greater lightsones.  give them to a gypsy in North Karana and she will give you a concordance of research which you can sell to a different gypsy for about 8 plat.  kill these guys until you hit lvl 16 and stop buy in Erudin to buy your spells at the libirary at lvl 12 buy; bind affintiy, burnout, and elemental: fire. at 16 buy summon throwing dagger, shielding, summon heartstone, phantom leather (requires a cat's eye agate for a reagent) buy shock of Flame, a 100 piont DD and Minor Summoning: water.<br>    Now use your riches to buy a stein of moggock and a Flowing Black Robe, and maybe some +int earring and rings from a jeweler.  offer some newbie 10plat to create a mule and kill fish in the water at the clerics guild and let you loot the corpses.  Give the fish corpse to the cleric in the pool and he'll give you a band of rochet nife, a +3Int +12mana ring.<br>   Go to Highpass Hold and kill gnolls, you may wish to join a group until you get to level 18, where you can solo gnolls and shout for a group on orc side where the mobs spawn fast and hit hard and a group of 4 or less will quickly be overwhelmed.  If you prefer a more laid back fight then stay with the gnolls, either way, when you hit 20 it's time to go again, stop by in .  Now head to South Karana and kill Aviaks until you get to 23.  You should go to the treants after that and kill them until 26.<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
