	   <tr><td colspan=2>I play a human mage, I tried playing a gnome or other races as a mage because of their high int byt quickly deleted them.  What I found though is that a human mage although low on int (I made mine with 100 int) have much better strength, and dex.  This is important because you will last a big longer in a melee, long enough usually for your cleric to heal you and your pet to save your butt.<br><br>Besides that you will have less issues with NPCs and always better prices with merchants.  Although only lvl 19 right now the gear I have purchased takes my int up to 123 right now.  I have been told i can take it all the way to 200 and from what I have read about equipment I think I can.<br><br>Properly equiped a human mage will be much easier to play than a non-human.<br><br>On another topic compared to other classess Mages really are the only self-sufficant players in the game.  We might not be the most powerful (although I think we may be in some instances), or the most desired in groups, or even respected, but I saw a lvl 30 mage solo a Sand Giant in Oassis... there werent many lvl 30 warrs or Wizzies that would.  We can be independant if we have to.<br><br>Just my thoughts.<br><br>-LordMelkor <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
