	   <tr><td colspan=2>Reread your post:<br><br>&gt;Um...why did you write this? Didn't you see my &gt;HUGE magician guide that took me 2 hours to &gt;write??<br><br>The above is being a jerk in anyone's book. He wrote his guide because he felt he had something to contribute. It is his opinion.  Maybe not the same as yours, but he has the right to post even though you have put out your guide.  Since your guide did not cover newbie type areas in Qeynos, his post seems like a fair post.<br><br><br><br>&gt;I definetely wouldn't suggest going to BB unless &gt;you are gonna fight giant snakes or elite &gt;gnolls. That zone IMO is the gathering of &gt;idiots...and trains are horrible there.<br><br>This is not a bad zone at the point he suggested. You just have to know where to fight.  Giant snake are great exp and good loot. But you can still get hit by trains.  There is a great room, however, with 3 gnolls that very few people vist.  It is a great place to solo with little interference from others.  Go to the tree with the trap floor on the main level outside (just to the left of the entrance). Cast invisible and drop through the trap into the water below.  Swim to the hallway out of sight of the gnolls. There are three that are there around the water.  Cast a pet in the hall, earth or water depending on your style.  The 3 gnolls should all be blue to you.  The one nearest to the hallway can be pulled without pulling the other 2.  Kill him first, med and get pet to full HP.  Wait for the remaining 2 gnolls to get to the end of the chamber away from the bridge at the other end.  Send your pet in to take on one of them.  The key here is to try to break up the spawn.  Kill one of the 2 gnolls and drag the fight out a little to kill the second one to spread the spawn.  When you are done you can sit in the room and take the spawns one at a time.  Rarely does anyone come in here and it is a dead end so no trains come through.  When you are done, gate out. You don't even have to bother learning the rest of the dungeon if you don't want to.  I've leveled two characters (one a magi) in this room.  You can go two levels here.  If the Mobs start conning green to you you need to watch out, they will run and bring friends. If one gets out, gate.<br><br>So I dont' see BB as a waste of time and would recommend it when played right.  I don't view this person's post as useless, just a different way to play the game.<br><br><br>&gt;Also, can you please use paragraphs when you &gt;right a guide....its really hard to read without &gt;em. <br><br>This was a useful piece of feedback.  Problem is it got lost in the attack you made in the first two lines.  Zuranthium, you have some good ideas, you just need to allow that people have opinions other than yours.  Like I said in my message below to you, others have as much right to post here as you do without having you come directly at them.  There are not enough people posting here yet that we can absorb these kind of comments.  The above poster will likely not post again and move to another board and we have potentially lost another person to support this board.<br><br>Cetus<br>The nameless<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Cetus<br>The Nameless</td></tr>
