<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9678249803944></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9678249803944><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=9678249803944>Kunark at 44+</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=9678249803944#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=450><span id=Sage>Sparr</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>113 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Sep 1st 12:16 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.66]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>For those of you that DO have Kunark, it is the place to be 44+, solo or grouped!  You have SO much more variety to choose from.  Theres Spirocs and Raptors in Timorous Deep, Forest Giants in Burning Woods, Keepers in Trakanons Teeth, and many more extremely common large area spawns that will be blue at 44 and continue being so all the way into the 50s.<br><br>For money Kunark is good too.  In Lake of Ill Omen there are two 2 hour spawns of level 40 shamen, both of whom drop weapons worth over 500pp (exact price server dependant).  In Burning Woods if you are hunting sarnaks outside Chardok you will pick up a Runic Carver within an hour of arrival every time you go.  In a full group in Trakanons Teeth with a druid to pull the Forager/Hunter/Nameds youll be brining in about 1 NICE rare item every hour to get your chance to random for.<br><br>PS: Yeah, I missed a LOT.  Kunark is big, I expect follow-ups.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
