<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9674651542690></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9674651542690><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=9674651542690>Errata</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=9674651542690#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Aug 28th 8:19 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>From my hunting experience on wisp island, it could get VERY uncomfortable at level 8.  Main reason is the wisps tend to circle the island and walk around the coast in bands.  More than one wisp on a level 8 wisp can equal out to pain and ouchies in a hurry.  Don't kill anything with kedge in the name there, makes the kerrans go sadistic on you.<br><br>Level 15 Monk in Lake Rathe:  Named Jonah Brucker or Brunker can't remember.  Damage shield works well here.  He has the same spawn time as Trissa Whistlesong, water and minor gems for loot, but rarely camped as most people don't consider the loot worth it.  Same exp as Trissa though.<br><br>One thing Corpusnuntia didn't mention is the bard Trissa Whistlesong in West Freeport in Hogcaller's Inn.  She is level 15, hits for low damage (comparatively) and only has one attack per round.  It MIGHT be possible for a level 12 magician to kill her, my experience is from a druid and I imagine it would be possible.  You will have TERRIBLE competition for this spawn, but the reward is awesome experience and at least 1pp in loot every time.  Another downside is negatory faction with Guards of Qeynos, Knights of Truth, and Antonican Bards.  This is not a massive hit though, my druid hunted her from 14 until 19 and is dubious to bards.<br><br>Hermit in SK:  Lots of competition!  Hits for 42 and double attacks, throws in a kick every couple of rounds.  About 1 in 6 times he will drop an FS: Scimitar, Shortsword, Longsword, or 2 Handed Sword.  Might drop the bastard and broadsword too, never had them in my experience.  He sometimes drops magician research items (pearl shard, ice of vellious), but do not count on these.  Great experience, gets mind numbingly boring.<br><br>Guards:  Take the time to learn which guards are uber newbie guards and which ones aren't.  Choice Butcherblock hunting is npc's not guards, seen a 51 magician friend die to a guard there, at some places it has a chance of being an uberguard or a normal guard (Delin's hut)  These npc's used to be really camped but people have seemed to calm down.<br><br>Aviak guards are not sometimes camped, they are 99.9% of the time camped.  Can be good exp though.<br><br>I told Zuranthium about the dwarf skeletons in Butcherblock ;)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
