<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96716024621739></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96716024621739><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=96716024621739>Extra info 44-50</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=96716024621739#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=684><span id=Sage>Eendyar</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>16 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 24th 7:37 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The easiest way to level from 44 to 48 is to kill spectres and sand giants in oasis.  Not only do you get fast experience, but you can make 100pp/hour just by killing them.<br><br>Seafury Cyclops's in OOT might give better experience but they have around 4000hp which is a full mana drain for a lvl 44-47 mage.  Not only that, but they resist the fire dd's somewhat so they arent the best thing to solo.  However grouped vs sea furies is much faster experience.<br><br>Ice giants are a good idea because they are the same level but more susceptible to fire attacks.  Not only that, but they are much easier to kill with jboots since everfrost is a big running zone unlike OOT (island).<br><br>Escape in everfrost is easy compared to escaping an island.<br><br>I'm still in oasis about to get 47, but watch out because those spectres are very easy to train.  And 3 or 4 can wreak havoc on many newbies in the zone.<br><br>SG's go down pretty fast if using an earth pet and shock of swords (44 dd magical).  Usually 4 shocks + pet with fire shield takes care of the problem.<br><br>Each spec usually takes 2 shocks and pet with fire shield, sometimes a Blaze (34 dd fire) is needed to finish a spec off.<br><br>Specs (1.5-1.8khp) Sg's(2-2.3khp)<br><br>Two to three specs can be killed per mana bar or upto two sg's.  <br><br>Great exp for the small downtime and its always nice to get a lockjaw now and then.<br><br>Very nice and informative post Zuranthium, just lengthy and a possible spoiler for mages who want to do some exploring of their own :)<br>&nbsp;<br>Eendyar Soulseeker<br>46'th High Elf Mage <br>"Mythic Synergy"<br><a href="http://www.mythicsynergy.com" target=_new>http://www.mythicsynergy.com</a><br>Fennin Ro</td></tr>
