	   <tr><td colspan=2>Thanks for the reply to my post Edndyar. I talked about killing spectors and the like in my guide, however I didn't recommnd doing it to your level. The problem I found with these guys, was that at level 46, over half of them were conning green, giving no exp. for the kill, or signficantly less. <br><br>Also, Oasis is ALWAYS really crowded and these things are HIGHLY camped, so thats sort of why I suggested Sea Furies. There usually won't be anyone at the seafuries. So even though it takes a lot longer to kill them, and you have a lot more downtime. You will be getting more exp. then if you were at Oasis, forced to group with a couple other people becuase its so crowded, and not getting exp.(or barely any) every other pull becuase they con green.<br><br>Also you mentioned something about not hunting Seafuries becuase their magic resist to fire was high. Well I won't suggest trying to take seafuries until level 44, which is when you get your new shock DD that isn't fire based.<br><br>I hope you like my guide. As you said it is 'a possible spoiler', however this is just a GUIDE and I would have to smack the person that did everything step by step, level by level, to what I said in here. I personally like to explore, which is how I found a few of the places that I listed in my guide, so I definetely wouldn't want any newbie to think its not good to travel and explore. Thanks all.<br><br>Zuranthium/Corpusnuntia/Divineshadow/Naltec/Natalos/Plantmaster/Sunsong<br><br>Player of many characters on the Nameless server.<br><br>Player who just hit level 30 the other day with his twink necromancer! =:-)<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
